<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> --EDIT--</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Didn't want to forget.<br>
<br>
Last night I got to witness enchanter brilliance at its finest.<br>
<br>
After dropping down to Level Three (LT), our tank (Vrazztak) went to pull the sage room so that we could break it. The Sage room is 4 spawns (2 Wizards, Sage/PH, Scribe/PH). Well, in the course of things, there were three adds. I don't believe anyone started the pull at FM, thinking 4 shouldn't require it....7 does.<br>
<br>
But it didn't.<br>
<br>
Somehow, we managed to take a train of 7, and reduce it to nothing but froggy corpses.<br>
<br>
No one died, tho I had like 15 HPs when all as said and done.<br>
<br>
Really, it all came down to beautiful crowd control, by Presea.<br>
<br>
I've heard stories of people claiming a good enchanter can stop a train dead in its track. I had never actually witnessed one, until last night. That was, simply, amazing.<br>
<br>
/cheer Presea<br>
<br>
Of course.. not too long thereafter, a train of at least 10 hit us, Presea was the first to die, and Resuscitates followed.<br>
<br>
An hour of CR later (I spent a great deal of time ressing the victims of that train, as it went all the way to zone) We were back in Sage Room kickin undead froggy @$$.<br>
<br>
All-in-all, a good night. Had a blast.<br>
<br>
Yabu didn't bring the booze tho.<br>
<br>
/glare Yabu.<br>
<br>
