<br>
I really enjoyed grouping with everyone.  Wazil, it was great finally meeting you! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   I'm glad that everything went smoothly (except for said train that took out just about half the zone).  <br>
<br>
You guys are going to give me a big head, though, if you keep telling me that I am such a leet Enchanter!  I think that anyone can be good at crowd control as an Enchanter as long as they have a good technique, and as long as they don't panic.  That is they key, not panicking and running around like a chicken with your head cut off while the tank runs around trying to taunt off the mob that is JUST out of range for taunt to work until finally the Enchanter is dead dead dead and shortly the rest of the party too because the tank was busy trying to save the Enchanter while all the other mobs were beating on the rest of the party when the Enchanter should have just stood still so the tank could taunt it or if the tank is busy there are these neat spells called Color Shift and Memory Blur that come in handy in situations like that so you can stop getting attacked and mez everything. <br>
/em takes a breath.<br>
Right...um, yeah =)<br>
<br>
Speaking of Color Shift, it's my area effect stun spell.  Last night, during that train, I used it.  Our tank was bringing 4 mobs.  I tried to mez one, but it kept hitting me so I decided to use Color Shift to make it stop for a second so I could mez it.  Well, just then the train was making its way in to our room. It gives me a message &quot;Target is stunned by the scintillating colors&quot; for each mob is effects.  I was excpecting to see about 3 or 4 in that message, but got more like 10.  Lets just say that's all that was on my chat area!  I was like &quot;oh crap!&quot; but it was too late and then I died.  That's my little story about the train, as it was all I got to see of it. =)<br>
<br>
And here's my story about leaving.  I decided that I wouldn't gate, as I was bound in the Overthere.  So I convinced Yabu to lead me out.  We IvU'ed and then started out.  Finally found the stairs, and we were off.  We found the bridge, but I lost him and started wandering around trying to find him.  Well, I didn't realize that there were gargoyles there, and guess what, they're not undead.  So they run for me, I panic (ha ha, I suck) and run away a little, then try to stun them and escape.  They keep interrupting me though and I die.  Yabu's plea for an EXP rez were met with silence, but luckily he was able to drag my body to zone.  I hate leaving a body when I log out, so I headed back to Lower Guk.  Luckily a nice Druid gave me a port to WC and a SoW for just a Clarity and Gift of Magic.  So I got there and looted all but my awesome Raw Silk Belt!  I figured it would be safe to leave that. =)  But I shouted one last time for an EXP rez, and lo and behold, a cleric showed up.  I asked him if he could give me an EXP rez and he said sure.  So he did, and I got a little EXP back.  Yay!  Still, I blame Belmonte. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
So I'm not worried about dying, I make it a point to die in every dungeon I enter.  I can give you a detailed account of every dungeon I have died in as well as an approximate number of times and locations <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I think we should go back.  I did eventually gate back to OT, but I'll come back.  Be back on Thursday night (but I work late so I will be on around 8:30pm Pacific.<br>
<br>
Again, nice work everyone!<br>
/applaud <br>
/clap<br>
/congratulate<br>
